          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between a social media dashboard and native analytics?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Native analytics (Meta Business Suite, LinkedIn Analytics, etc.) show you data for a single platform only. A social media dashboard aggregates data from all your platforms in one place, enabling cross-platform comparison and consolidated reporting. It also typically allows custom date ranges and exportable reports that native tools restrict.</p></div></div>
          </div>
